        "content": "<p>I would like to have an argument which is the dependency of a later argument be an <code>autoParam</code>. Unfortunately, since <code>autoParam</code>s cannot be implicit (right?), I don't know if there is a way to apply my function such that the <code>autoParam</code> is, in fact, inferred. Here is a short MWE:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kd\">theorem</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">justTheSame</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">{</span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Array</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Nat</span><span class=\"o\">}</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">{</span><span class=\"n\">i</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Nat</span><span class=\"o\">}</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">il</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">i</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">&lt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a.size</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kd\">by</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">omega</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">h</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">i</span><span class=\"o\">]</span><span class=\"bp\">'</span><span class=\"n\">il</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">i</span><span class=\"o\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">h</span>\n\n<span class=\"kd\">variable</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">A</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Array</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Nat</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">I</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Fin</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">A.size</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">h</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">A</span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">I</span><span class=\"o\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"o\">)</span>\n<span class=\"c\">/-</span>\n<span class=\"cm\">application type mismatch</span>\n<span class=\"cm\">  justTheSame h</span>\n<span class=\"cm\">argument</span>\n<span class=\"cm\">  h</span>\n<span class=\"cm\">has type</span>\n<span class=\"cm\">  A[I] = 1 : Prop</span>\n<span class=\"cm\">but is expected to have type</span>\n<span class=\"cm\">  autoParam (?m.683 &lt; Array.size ?m.682) _autoâœ : Prop</span>\n<span class=\"cm\">-/</span>\n<span class=\"k\">#check</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">justTheSame</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">h</span>\n\n<span class=\"k\">#check</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">justTheSame</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">_</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">h</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"c1\">-- works</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>Is it possible to omit <code>_</code> in the application?</p>\n<p>(UPDATE: Not really resolved, but there is already another thread mentioned below.)</p>",
